================================================================================
ARCHITECTURE NOTES
================================================================================

PATTERNS:
  - Games are independent engines with their own state structs
  - UI rendering is separate from game logic (screens/ directory)
  - The App struct in app/mod.rs bridges games, UI, and services
  - Theme is centralized in ui/theme.rs
  - Save/load goes through services/save.rs -> storage/local.rs

ADDING A NEW GAME:
  1. Create src/games/<name>/mod.rs with game engine struct
  2. Add rendering in src/ui/screens/<name>.rs
  3. Add enum variant in app/mod.rs View enum
  4. Wire up key handling in app/mod.rs handle_* methods
  5. Add to header tabs in ui/components/header.rs
  6. Add to draw_main match in ui/mod.rs
  7. Register in mod.rs files

ADDING A NEW THEME:
  1. Add method to ProxTheme in ui/theme.rs
  2. Select it via app settings
  3. Pass theme ref through all draw calls (already done)

ADDING STATS:
  1. Add field to PlayerStats in models/stats.rs
  2. Add serialization support (already have #[derive(Serialize, Deserialize)])
  3. Track the stat in app/mod.rs apply_*_outcome methods
  4. Display in screens/dashboard.rs or game screens

BORROW CHECKER NOTES:
  - When calling self.draw() inside self.state.hand.push(self.draw()), extract
    to let card = self.draw() first, then push(card)
  - Vec<Line> instead of Vec<Span> for Paragraph::new() in ratatui 0.27
  - Use ratatui::text::Line and Span for styled text

